steps.instruction:
For a more step-by-step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2011/06/03/no-knead-cheese-burger-buns-so-easy-so-cheesy)

### Prep
- Finely grate the sharp cheddar 
    - If using fresh grated cheese, then use 1 teaspoon of salt

### Steps
1. Combine all of the dough ingredients, and beat at high speed, using an electric mixer, for 2 minutes
2. Place the dough in a lightly greased bowl or rising bucket, cover it, and let it rise for 60 to 90 minutes, until it's noticeably puffy
3. Gently deflate the dough, and divide it into 6 pieces; each will be about 111g, a scant 4 ounces
4. Shape the dough into balls, and place them in the wells of a lightly greased hamburger bun pan. If you don't have a bun pan, space them on a lightly greased or parchment-lined baking sheet
5. Gently flatten the buns with your hand to fill the bottom of the pan's wells, or until they're about 3 1/2" to 4" wide
6. Cover the buns, and let them rise for 60 to 90 minutes, until they're noticeably puffy
7. Towards the end of the rising time, preheat the oven to 350F
8. Brush each bun with some of the melted butter.
9. Bake the buns for 16 to 19 minutes, until they're a light, golden brown, and their interior temperature is at least 190F, measured with an instant-read thermometer
10. Remove the buns from the oven, transfer them to a rack, and brush with the remaining melted butter. Allow the buns to cool completely, then store airtight at room temperature.

ingredients.note: If using freshly grated cheese, use 1 teaspoon
Use 3/4 cup of water for when its cold and dry
